<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF0FF99FEB1F991FB0051F3" blockId="5.[192,1441,1555,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF0FF99FEB1F991FEAF5137" box="[256,354,1592,1618]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF0FF99FEDAF99EFDF15137" box="[363,572,1591,1618]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Minas Gerais State</collectingRegion>
, Lassance, Harmony Farm; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF0FF99FCDFF991FB8F5137" box="[878,1090,1591,1618]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" value="2017-11-21">21 November 2017</date>
; M. A. F. Malacco. Host:? 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FAEFF99EFF125111" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF0FF99FAEFF99EFA6C5134" box="[1374,1441,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Idiops</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FF5DF9F3FE975110" box="[236,346,1626,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Idiopidae</taxonomicName>
) [det. 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF0FF99FE11F9F3FE785111" box="[416,437,1626,1652]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">R</collectionCode>
. Bertani, IBB, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF0FF99FDE2F9F3FD0F5111" box="[595,706,1626,1652]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Brazil], adult or subadult female. The wasp stood over the immobilized armored trapdoor spider as it laid ventral side upward on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF0FF99FBAEF9D5FB0C51F3" author="Malacco MAF" box="[1055,1217,1660,1686]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="533776460307128" refId="ref25474" refString="Malacco MAF. 2017. Marimbondo cacador com sua presa, uma aranha. Available athttps: // www. facebook. com / fazharmonia / photos / a. 378117119206397 / 533776460307128 /. (Last accessed 10 November 2021)." type="journal article" year="2017">Malacco 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF0FF99FEB1F936FDC4507A" blockId="5.[192,1441,1555,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF0FF99FEB1F936FEAF51DC" box="[256,354,1695,1721]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF0FF99FEC0F937FD8E51DD" box="[369,579,1694,1720]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Pernambuco State</collectingRegion>
, Buíque; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF0FF99FD04F937FCBD51DD" box="[693,880,1694,1721]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" value="2020-08-28">28 August 2020</date>
, 1544 EDT; C. Avenengo. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FB49F937FA6D51DD" authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[1272,1440,1694,1720]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Acanthoscurria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF0FF99FB49F937FA6D51DD" box="[1272,1440,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Acanthoscurria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF0FF99FF7AF968FEF551BE" box="[203,312,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">natalensis</emphasis>
Chamberlin (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FE65F968FDB251B9" box="[468,639,1729,1756]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult male [det. 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF0FF99FCFAF968FCAD51BE" box="[843,864,1729,1755]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">R</collectionCode>
. Bertani,]. The wasp grasped the Natal brown birdeater by the base of the femur of its right foreleg with her mandibles and dragged it, dorsal side upward, across the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF0FF99FEFAF8ACFE33507A" author="Avenengo C." box="[331,510,1797,1823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" refId="ref21117" refString="Avenengo C. 2020. Tarantula hawk-Wasps and Allies (Subfamily Pepsinae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 66039828. (Last accessed 15 December 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Avenengo 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF0FF99FEB1F881FAA250E3" blockId="5.[192,1441,1555,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF0FF99FEB1F881FE5E5027" box="[256,403,1832,1858]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF0FF99FE2CF88EFDB35027" box="[413,638,1831,1858]" country="Colombia" name="Tolima" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Tolima Department</collectingRegion>
, Ibagué, Vereda El Gallo trail; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF0FF99FC65F881FBA25027" box="[980,1135,1831,1858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" value="2017-04-27">27 April 2017</date>
; A. 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF0FF99FB2AF881FB7D5027" box="[1179,1200,1832,1858]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">R</collectionCode>
. Reinoso. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FAD4F881FE985001" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Pamphobeteus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF0FF99FAD4F881FEE05001" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Pamphobeteus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF0FF99FED6F8E3FDDF5000" box="[359,530,1866,1893]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp pulled the paralyzed tarantula backwards across the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping the base of its pedipalp with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF0FF99FB74F8C5FAAE50E3" author="Reinoso AR" box="[1221,1379,1900,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" refId="ref26273" refString="Reinoso AR. 2017. Wasp and tarantula. Available at https: // www. instagram. com / p / BTaVY 6 uAcz 3 /." type="url" year="2017">Reinoso 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF3FF9AFEB1FF7FFBD55656" blockId="6.[192,1441,214,307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF3FF9AFEB1FF7FFEB35795" box="[256,382,214,240]" name="Saint Lucia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">ST. LUCIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFE38FF7FFDF55795" box="[393,568,214,240]" country="Saint Lucia" name="Praslin" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Praslin Quarter</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFF3FF9AFDF5FF7FFDB35795" box="[580,638,214,240]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
NW 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFD0CFF7FFCC05795" box="[701,781,214,240]" country="Saint Lucia" name="Praslin" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Praslin</collectingRegion>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF3FF9AFCA8FF7FFC635795" box="[793,942,214,240]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" value="2007-06-10">10 June 2007</date>
; J. LaPergola. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFB23FF7FFEC35677" authority="Husser" authorityName="Husser" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Tapinauchenius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polybote">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF3FF9AFB23FF7FFA6C5795" box="[1170,1441,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Tapinauchenius polybote</emphasis>
Hüsser
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFEACFF5EFE055677" box="[285,456,247,274]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult female. The wasp examined the immobilized tarantula with her mouthparts and antennae as it laid, dorsal side upward, on the bare ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF3FF9AFCE8FEB0FBC15656" author="LaPergola J." box="[857,1036,281,307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref25159" refString="LaPergola J. 2007. Tarantula-hawk Wasps and Allies (Subfamily Pepsinae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 69961496. (Last accessed 22 February 2021)." type="url" year="2007">LaPergola 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
